<doc id="738077" wikidata="Q918337" url="?curid=738077" title="Unicast">
<text>In computer networking, unicast is a one-to-one transmission from one point in the network to another point; that is, one sender and one receiver, each identified by a network address.

Unicast is in contrast to multicast and broadcast which are one-to-many transmissions.

Internet Protocol unicast delivery methods such as Transmission Control Protocol (TCP) and User Datagram Protocol (UDP) are typically used.

==See also==
* Anycast
* Broadcast, unknown-unicast and multicast traffic
* IP address
* IP multicast
* Routing

