<doc id="738083" wikidata="Q3736413" url="?curid=738083" title="Wenno von Rohrbach">
<text>Wenno von Rohrbach, also known as Winno, Vinno, and Winne, was the first Master (&quot;Herrenmeister&quot;) of the Livonian Brothers of the Sword, leading the Order from 1204 to 1209.

== Death ==
Originally from Kassel-Naumburg, Wenno was killed by the knight with an axe, in a quarrel caused by some unknown reason. As a result, Wickbert was sentenced to death. Wenno was succeeded by Volkwin Schenk.

